en.purpose: To record additional composition metadata aligned with IHE-XDS which is not already available from the Reference Model COMPOSITION class.
en.use: Use to add IHE-XDS aligned metadata to a COMPOSITION.context, which along with existing COMPOSITION attributes, allows the composition to be registered in an IHE-XDS environment.

at0000.description: Additional composition metadata aligned with IHE-XDS which is not already available from the Reference Model COMPOSITION class.

at0001.description: The speciality of the author/composer of the document.

at0002.description: A high-level document class code, normally selected from a valueset provided by the IHE-XDS Affinity Domain.
at0002.comment:
For example: Report, Summary, Images, Plan, Patient Preferences, Workflow.
These codes are specific to an XDS Affinity Domain.

at0003.description: The code specifying the precise type of document from the user perspective. Normally selected from a valueset provided by the local IHE-XDS Affinity Domain or national standard.
at0003.comment:
for example:  Pulmonary History and Physical, Discharge Summary, Ultrasound Report.
These codes are specific to an XDS Affinity Domain.

at0004.description: A term specifying the level of confidentiality of the XDS Document.
at0004.comment: Coded text is preferred, normally specific to an XDS Affinity Domain.

at0009.description: The code specifying the clinical specialty where the act that resulted in the document was performed.
at0009.comment:
For example: Family Practice, Laboratory, Radiology.
Coded text is preferred, normally specific to an XDS Affinity Domain.

at0010.description: Additional metadata about the document itself, including size, url.

at0011.description: This list of codes represents the main clinical acts.

at0000.text: PAINAD-Sp, escala de valoración del dolor en pacientes con demencia
at0000.description: PAINAD-Sp, escala de valoración del dolor en pacientes con demencia

at0004.description: Respiración (independiente de la verbalización-vocalización del dolor)

at0006.text: Respiración ocasionalmente dificultosa / Periodos cortos de hiperventilación

at0007.text: Respiración dificultosa y ruidosa / Largos periodos de hiperventilación / Respiración de CheyneStokes

at0010.text: Gemidos o quejidos ocasionales / Habla con volumen bajo o con desaprobación

at0011.text: Llamadas agitadas y repetitivas / Gemidos y quejidos en volumen alto / Llanto

at0018.text: Tenso / Camina de forma angustiada / No para quieto con las manos

at0019.text: Rígido / Puños cerrados / Rodillas flexionadas / Agarra o empuja / Agresividad física

at0021.text: No necesita que se le consuele

at0022.text: Se le distrae o se le tranquiliza hablándole o tocándole

at0023.text: Es imposible consolarle, distraerle o tranquilizarle

at0000.text: PAINAD, Paint Assessment in Advanced Dementia
at0000.description: PAINAD, Paint Assessment in Advanced Dementia

at0006.text: Occasional labored breathing / Short period of hyperventilation

at0007.text: Noisy labored breathing / Long period of hyperventilation / Cheyne-Stokes respirations

at0010.text: Occasional moan or groan / Low-level speech with a negative or disapproving quality

at0011.text: Repeated troubled calling out / Loud moaning or groaning / Crying

at0019.text: Rigid / Fists clenched / Knees pulled up / Pulling or pushing away / Striking out

at0022.text: Distracted or reassured by voice or touch

at0023.text: Unable to console, distract or reassure
